text: Minnesota Governor Tim Walz has announced that he is ending his campaign for reelection
a decision that was made public on January 6, 2026
This development comes as a significant change in the state's upcoming election landscape
Governor Walz, who has been in office since 2019, had previously indicated his intention to seek another term
but has now reversed that decision
The news of his withdrawal from the race is expected to have implications for the field of candidates
vying for the governor's seat in the upcoming election
